{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781116286712,"sessionID":"ses_14d3aebd9ffepOyCns3UtoeLoF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_k5nzezx5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"README.md","content":"```markdown\n# Temperature Converter CLI\n\nThis CLI tool provides functions to convert temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.\n\n## Installation\n```bash\npip install .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Conversion Commands\n- Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit:\n  ```bash\n  python -m converters celsius_to_fahrenheit 25\n  ```\n- Convert Fahrenheit to Celsius:\n  ```bash\n  python -m converters fahrenheit_to_celsius 77\n  ```\n- Convert Celsius to Kelvin:\n  ```bash\n  python -m converters celsius_to_kelvin 25\n  ```\n\n### Batch Conversion\nConvert multiple values at once:\n```bash\npython -m converters celsius_to_fahrenheit 25 30 35\n```\n\n## Tests\nThe tests in `test_converters.py` ensure correctness for:\n- `celsius_to_fahrenheit`\n- `fahrenheit_to_celsius`\n- `celsius_to_kelvin`\n\nRun tests with:\n```bash\npython -m unittest test_converters\n```\n\nMIT License\n```python\n# This file is part of the Temperature Converter CLI.\n# It is distributed under the MIT License.\n```"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws3/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws3/README.md","time":{"start":1781116286704,"end":1781116286711}},"id":"prt_eb2cdb6e3001CUhmYdTSB10jjj","sessionID":"ses_14d3aebd9ffepOyCns3UtoeLoF","messageID":"msg_eb2cb8a06001WX2FlWn4ES9Y4C"}}
